<?xml version='1.0' encoding='ISO-8859-1' ?>
<grammar>
<section>
<title> Past simple of &lt;i&gt;be:&lt;/i&gt; questions</title>
<sectiontitle> In the question, we use &lt;i&gt;Was I/he/she/it ...?&lt;/i&gt; and&lt;i&gt; Were you/we/they ...?&lt;/i&gt;</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>sta_gram9_2_1.mp3</titlesound>
<text1> </text1>
<text1a>&lt;b&gt;Was I&lt;/b&gt; quiet?</text1a>
<sound1>sta_gram9_2_2.mp3</sound1>
<text2> </text2>
<text2a>&lt;b&gt; Were&lt;/b&gt; they dangerous?</text2a>
<sound2>sta_gram9_2_3.mp3</sound2>
<sectiontitle2>We can also ask questions with &lt;i&gt;wh-&lt;/i&gt; question words (&lt;i&gt;where, what, when&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;who&lt;/i&gt; etc.).</sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2>sta_gram9_2_4.mp3</titlesound2>
<text3> </text3>
<text3a>&lt;b&gt; Where were&lt;/b&gt; you? In France.</text3a>
<sound3>sta_gram9_2_5.mp3</sound3>
<text4> </text4>
<text4a>&lt;b&gt; Who was&lt;/b&gt; that lady? That was my mother.</text4a>
<sound4>sta_gram9_2_6.mp3</sound4>
</section>
<section>
<title> Past simple of &lt;i&gt;be:&lt;/i&gt; questions</title>
<sectiontitle> We can answer Past simple &lt;i&gt;yes/no&lt;/i&gt; questions with short answers.</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>sta_gram9_2_7.mp3</titlesound>
<text1>&lt;b&gt;Were&lt;/b&gt; you a servant?   </text1>
<text1a>No, I &lt;b&gt;wasn't.&lt;/b&gt;</text1a>
<sound1>sta_gram9_2_8.mp3</sound1>
<text2> &lt;b&gt;Was&lt;/b&gt; he English?  </text2>
<text2a> Yes, he &lt;b&gt;was&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;b&gt; </text2a>
<sound2>sta_gram9_2_9.mp3</sound2>
<sectiontitle2>We can also use &lt;i&gt;was&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;were&lt;/i&gt; with &lt;i&gt;there.&lt;/i&gt;</sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2>sta_gram9_2_10.mp3</titlesound2>
<text3>How many people &lt;b&gt;were there?&lt;/b&gt;</text3>
<text3a>&lt;b&gt; There were&lt;/b&gt; lots of people. </text3a>
<sound3>sta_gram9_2_11.mp3</sound3>
<text4> How many ships &lt;b&gt;were there?&lt;/b&gt;</text4>
<text4a>&lt;b&gt; There was&lt;/b&gt; only one. </text4a>
<sound4>sta_gram9_2_12.mp3</sound4>
</section>
</grammar>